FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Government Statements): Recovery of duty on
business cars
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Businesses are to be able to recover VAT paid on the purchase of cars bought
wholly for business purposes - primarily leasing - from August 1 1995. In
these cases, businesses will have to charge VAT when they sell the car.
Customs and Excise said it was proposed to introduce a provision that only
50 per cent of the VAT applying to car leasing charges can be recovered
where there is any use of the car for private motoring.
