<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Government Statements): VAT scheme for
second-hand goods
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Businesses dealing in second-hand goods will come under the European
Community (EC) Seventh VAT Directive on second-hand goods. From January 1
1995 the margin scheme of accounting for VAT will be extended to all
second-hand goods, works of art, antiques and collectors' items except
precious metals and gemstones.
An effective reduced VAT rate of 2.5 per cent will be introduced on imports
of certain works of art, antiques and collectors' items currently exempt
from VAT at import.
Any supplies of goods made through agents, including auctioneers, when
acting in their own names, will be treated for VAT purposes as supplies made
to them and by them.
An accounting scheme for auctioneers will be introduced which will ensure
they continue to pay VAT only on their fees.
</TEXT>
