<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Government Statements): Loophole closed on EC
share issues
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The issue of shares within the EU is exempt from VAT, which means that
traders making an issue cannot reclaim the VAT on any associated costs. VAT
avoidance schemes have been set up to avoid this by selling a few shares
outside the EU, because VAT on the costs of selling shares to purchasers
outside the EU is recoverable.
From accounting periods starting on or after December 1 1994, businesses
will have to identify more precisely the VAT they incur on shares issued
outside the EU.
</TEXT>
