<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Government Statements): Tax avoidance scheme
blocked
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A tax avoidance scheme on share issues was blocked within the amendments to
close tax avoidance loopholes. Changes were announced to the rules on VAT
and incidental financial transactions, which is estimated to cost up to
Pounds 100m a year. In addition to revenue protection, the move will bring
UK law in this area into line with European Community law. The changes will
come into effect from December 1 1994.
</TEXT>
