children is at university and another is doing A-levels.
Politics: Not committed, but feels Kenneth Clarke has done a good job as
chancellor.
Said yesterday: 'There were encouraging remarks regarding interest rates,
dispelling some of the pessimism in the City. He has recognised that our
industry has a major problem on excise duty differential resulting in
illegal bootlegging and lost jobs but to expect the European Community to
work together to harmonise duty and resolve a peculiarly British problem is
pretty naive.'
