schools have become technology colleges. Additional money will be provided
for the programme: Pounds 15m in 1995-96, rising to Pounds 20m and Pounds
25m in the following years to extend the programme to secondary schools
wishing to develop a special strength in foreign languages. The programme,
which has up to now been limited to grant-maintained and voluntary aided
schools, will be open to all maintained secondary schools. By 1997-98, the
Department hopes over 200 schools will be taking part in the programme.
