<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Their Budget): Superstore manager
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Richard Woodall, 29: general manager of the Norwich branch of Asda. Married
with two small children. Earns: Pounds 38,000 plus car.
Politics: 'Staunch' Tory.
Wanted: From a personal point of view, no increase in petrol duty. Hoped for
a generous budget which would return consumer confidence. Said yesterday:
The cuts in public spending mean there can probably be tax cuts next year.
From a business point of view it probably means at Asda we are going to have
the lowest-cost Christmas in relative terms since 1966.
</TEXT>
