<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Their Budget): Unemployed man
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Peter Chapman, 39: design engineer made redundant after 23 years at Tyneside
shipbuilder Swan Hunter with a pay off of just over Pounds 3,500. Children
aged 13 and 14.
Earns: Total weekly family income is Pounds 183.
Politics: Labour party member.
Said yesterday: 'He hasn't done anything to address the issues I'd have
liked. He's attacking the benefits on one side, with the change on mortgage
interest for people on income support and encouraging a low paid economy on
the other; it isn't beneficial for anybody.'
