<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Their Budget): Marketing executive
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
David Rist, 36. Marketing director of British Shoe Corporation, parent
company of Hush Puppies, married with a small baby. He declines to say how
much he earns but is 'comfortably affluent'. Politics: Voted Conservative
the last couple of times but is not committed. Wanted: A neutral Budget: He
said: 'Tax increases are simply not on the agenda.'
Said yesterday: 'We are fairly satisfied. There are a few things in it to
make people happier, and no major shocks. It seems to be pretty neutral. I'm
very relieved there has been no hike in interest rates. As a retailer, we
certainly welcome the transitional relief on business rates. I didn't expect
any significant tax reductions. Public expenditure seems to be under control
and the measures will hopefully instill a little bit of the feel-good
factor.'
