FT  30 NOV 94 / Budget 94 (Their Budget): The Lloyd's Name
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sara Gibb: Group Secretary to the Gooda Walker Action Group; a widow with
one daughter at university.
Wanted: Tax reform: 'It is ridiculous that someone earning Pounds 40,000
pays 40 per cent after Pounds 22,000, the same way as someone earning Pounds
400,000.'
Said yesterday: 'I would have preferred to see some real reform in income
tax - the marginal tax rate raised, say, to 50 per cent or 60 per cent for
people earning more than Pounds 60,000 a year. I am very disappointed they
did not rescind the VAT on fuel. To give these rebates just confirms they
should not have imposed the tax in the first place.'
