<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 94 / Observer: Hoarse laughter
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
They must be feeling pretty flat in Newmarket after seeing the latest
official perk granted to South Africa's small but influential racing
industry. Henceforth, the purchase of a racehorse is to be completely tax
deductible. The capital cost can be written off against tax at a flat 25 per
cent per year depreciation over four years. The new legislation even allows
owners unhappy with their horses' performance to stay happy. When a
racehorse is retired from active competition, its entire purchase price
immediately becomes claimable against tax.
A case of South Africa's Finance Department attempting to re-open the stable
door after the winnings have bolted?
</TEXT>
