   KATHMANDU
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Nepal's Communist party leader Man Mohan Adhikary said yesterday that King
Birendra had appointed him as the Himalayan nation's prime minister. 'I will
be sworn in tomorrow,' Mr Adhikary said as he left a meeting with the king.
Mr Adhikary's Communist Unified Marxist-Leninist (UML) party won a majority
