FT  30 NOV 94 / World News in Brief: Buster Edwards dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Great train robber Buster Edwards, 62, was found hanged in a lock-up garage
near the flower stall he ran at Waterloo station in London. Police said
there were no suspicious circumstances. In 1988 Edwards was portrayed by
rock singer Phil Collins in Buster, a film of his life.
